The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Hi-tech centre in design hub

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 Ahmedabad, Dec. 7: President A.P.J. Abdul Kalam will inaugurate a high-tech design vision centre at the National Institute of Design on January 5 on the occasion of its 25th convocation celebrations.

 The Rs 5-crore design centre is the first of its kind in the country and is equipped with facilities that will cater to the needs of students and also NID alumni, especially those who are independent design consultants and had to go overseas to avail such hi-tech design labs. 

 Darlie Koshy, the institute?s executive director, said the design centre would also give a boost to the NID for applied design research and product innovation for the industry. The lab would also support product development activities of the National Design Business Incubator in the campus.

 The institute has also lined up a series of programmes for its convocation celebrations. Kalam will deliver the convocation address and also inaugurate an exhibition, Hands On, Minds On, besides inaugurating the design outlet for students. 

 Koshy said the ministry of commerce and industry is expected to spell out a national design policy soon. 




